busdesc: UnitedHealth Group Incorporated operates as a diversified health care company in the United States. It operates through four segments: UnitedHealthcare, OptumHealth, OptumInsight, and OptumRx.
Lexmark International, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, operates as a developer, manufacturer, and supplier of printing, imaging, device management, and document workflow solutions.
Brunswick Corporation designs, manufactures, and markets recreation products worldwide.
Marathon Oil Corporation operates as an independent exploration and production company in the United States and Equatorial Guinea.
Nordstrom, Inc., a fashion retailer, provides apparels, shoes, cosmetics, and accessories for women, men, young adults, and children.

Ross Stores, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, operates off-price retail apparel and home fashion stores under the Ross Dress for Less and dd's DISCOUNTS brands. Its stores primarily offers apparel, accessories, footwear, and home fashions.
Halliburton Company provides a range of services and products to oil and natural gas companies worldwide.

Cooper Industries plc manufactures and sells electrical components and tools in the United States and internationally. It operates in two segments, Energy and Safety Solutions, and Electrical Products Group.
Ecolab Inc. provides water, hygiene, and energy technologies and services worldwide.
Dillard's, Inc. operates retail department stores primarily in the Southeastern, Southwestern, and Midwestern areas of the United States.
SUPERVALU INC., together with its subsidiaries, operates as a grocery wholesaler and retailer in the United States and internationally. It operates through two segments, Wholesale and Retail.
Ulta Beauty, Inc. operates as a beauty retailer in the United States.
Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc., together with its subsidiaries, operates as a hotel and leisure company worldwide.

Equinix (Nasdaq: EQIX) is the world's digital infrastructure company, enabling digital leaders to harness a trusted platform to bring together and interconnect the foundational infrastructure that powers their success.
Meredith Corporation operates as a diversified media company primarily in the United States. It operates in two segments, National Media and Local Media.

Emerson Electric Co. designs and manufactures technology and engineering products for industrial, commercial, and consumer markets worldwide. It operates through Automation Solutions and Commercial & Residential Solutions segments.
Prologis, Inc. is the global leader in logistics real estate with a focus on high-barrier, high-growth markets.
Viatris Inc., a healthcare company, manufactures and distributes various medicines for patients in the United States and internationally.
Digital Realty supports the world's leading enterprises and service providers by delivering the full spectrum of data center, colocation and interconnection solutions.
TransDigm Group Incorporated designs, produces, and supplies aircraft components in the United States and internationally.

XTO Energy Inc. extracts natural gas from shale and other tight formations. It also produces crude oil and natural gas liquids in the United States. The company owns interests in various oil and natural gas wells in the United States. XTO Energy Inc.
Healthpeak Properties, Inc. is a fully integrated real estate investment trust (REIT) and S&P 500 company.
